        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Sensor Resistance</title>
            <para>The sensor circuit resistance must be between 500 and 2000 ohms. Measure resistance at the sensor
                connector, or at the pins on the ECU connector, as follows:
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn ignition OFF.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To measure resistance at the pins on ECU connector, disconnect the ECU connector from
                    the ECU.
                </para>
                <para>To measure resistance at the sensor connector, disconnect the sensor from the sensor extension
                    cable.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure output at the pins indicated in Sensor Check Pins Table.</para>
                <para>If measurement is not between 500 and 2000 ohms, replace the sensor.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
